<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>i would hold off committing to the mage epic until you have a &quot;rare&quot; piece such as hate staff and air crown.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
pretty good advice. having one of the rarer pieces can really serve as a catalyst for pursuing the epic. I was blessed (burdened?) with the pegasus feather cloak at level 23, and from then on, the epic was something I felt I <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>had</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> to have or else my EQ experience would never be complete. and yes, the hate staff was the last piece I needed, and yes it was frustrating. many days were frustrating, but other days make it so worth it...like the day I bought the crown and Phinny finally dropped the water staff. same day. what a day. and then when you finally get it, and cast it...the most satisfying moment for me in EQ was finishing my epic. yes, I took a screenshot of the Master of Elements text, heh.<br>
<br>
if you decide not to pursue it, it's not a big deal. there are many primary hand items out there just as good or better for stats, and the 61+ pets do out damage the epic pet, so you're not going to be seriously gimped if you don't do it. but if you get one of the harder pieces, by all means, go for it. rather than the be all end all pet, the epic has become situational in Planes of Power, and that's probably a good thing. I haven't seen the new earth pets yet, but I do know that with a shaman backing him up with slows and heals, a buffed epic pet can tank mobs in Plane of Valor. and to me that is pretty impressive for a lvl 49 pet. he may con light blue, but he certainly doesn't suck. I don't regret the lost sleep and stress from pursuing the epic. just because it's not the big deal it used to be, doesn't mean it's still not a big deal.<br>
<br>
btw those of you wondering where people get earth staffs for MQ, check with your local uber guilds. they probably don't have anything banked as a guild to sell, but you may find that individuals have the staff from xping or gem farming in the planes. I myself got my MQ from a cleric, heh.<br>
